  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <p><seg type="diplomatic" subtype="address"><seg type="diplomatic" subtype="intitulatio">M<ex>alcolm</ex>, king of the Scots</seg>, to all worthy men of his entire land, <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="salutation">greeting.</seg></seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="disposition">I instruct that anywhere the prior of Coldingham or his servants shall be able
                  to find fugitives legitimately belonging to Coldingham, they
                  may lawfully have them without disturbance and harrassment; <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="injunction">and I forbid that anyone of you unlawfully withhold them, on pain of my
                     prohibition</seg>.</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="witnesses">As witnesses: Walter the chancellor, Hugh de Morville.</seg> <seg type="diplomatic" subtype="dating">At Berwick.</seg></p>
      </div>
    </body>
